  "updated_summary": "Seated on a wooden bench at night, AJ SHAHEEL, clad in a black suit and cap, playfully bantered with Sharky, sporting an 'AUSTRALIA' hat and sunglasses, and Kenny, in a black beanie and beige outdoor gear. On-screen text like 'AJ IS THE BEST' underscored their camaraderie as Sharky and Kenny chanted, \"AJ is the goat! He's better than the rest! AJ is the best!\" Sharky patted AJ SHAHEEL's back while Kenny feigned distress, both laughing amidst the chanting. AJ SHAHEEL explained the chant's origin, noting a shift from dislike to admiration, culminating in a four-time rendition to signify their changed perception. The group cheered, AJ SHAHEEL raised his arm, and a voice expressed enjoyment of the moment. The scene then shifted to an aerial view of 'Nics Retreat', a remote campsite in a dense forest, with a narrator stating the boys would be taken inside for the night. Inside a rustic indoor shelter, AJ SHAHEEL announced that only two people would leave the Outback, playfully critiquing the team's rice and beans meal. Kenny defended their efforts, stating they used only available ingredients, while Sharky agreed. AJ SHAHEEL questioned if they could have asked 'Nick', but Kenny cited rules. Chunkz intervened to calm the situation, and Kenny admitted the food was 'mid'. AJ SHAHEEL further described it as 'more mid than rice, undercooked rice and beans', which Kenny disputed, though AJ SHAHEEL claimed he could smell it. AJ SHAHEEL then declared a draw, surprising Kenny, while Sharky suggested a rematch, which Kenny declined, leading to laughter in the cozy, dimly lit shelter."
